<p>Hello Rheylent!</p>
<p>Welcome to the wiki, happy to have you here! I learned about the wiki through CB as well - it's a really fun game, and it's always cool to check out what all of our talented content creators create! Now that you have an account, you can be one of those content creators if you choose to do so, but there is no rush to do so. Getting started by reading, voting, and commenting is always a great option.</p>
<p>Speaking of, down below I've left you with my reading list to help get you started. I hope you enjoy your time here - feel free to reach out if you ever need anything!</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+Here&nbsp;are&nbsp;some&nbsp;places&nbsp;to&nbsp;start.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-Hope&nbsp;this&nbsp;helps!</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Maybe you've already seen these before, maybe you haven't, but hopefully something here is of use to you. Of course, if you have any questions, feel free to reach out!</p>
<p>The newest, freshest material can be found on the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/most-recently-created">Most Recently Created</a> page. If that updates a little too frequently for you though and you want more of a look at what remains popular, you can also try the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/top-rated-pages-this-month">Top Rated New Pages</a>.</p>
<p>If you want to see what other folks in the community like, there's the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/user-curated-lists">User-Curated Lists</a>. Here you can find things the community has put together and deemed a good read. Or maybe you want to give some underrated articles some love? Try out the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/young-and-under-30">Underread and Underrated</a> page.</p>
<p>Enjoy large hubs and working your way through them? Some cool hubs include the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/guide-hub">Guide Hub</a> for things that cover the Site itself, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/news">Site News Hub</a> for updates on all sorts of monthly Site content, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/canon-hub">Canon Hub</a> for all the various canons, <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/goi-formats">GoI Format Hub</a> for all your GoI needs, and <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/foundation-tales">Tales Hub</a> for your favorite tales.</p>
<p>Finally, if you find an author you love from any of this and want to see more from them, you can find them in the <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/members-pages">Authors' Pages</a> section. If they're not on that list, try the statistic site, <a href="http://scpper.com">scpper.com</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

